Sentencas: La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) is a common cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells because of its excellent oxygen reduction reaction catalytic activity.
Titulo: LaCrO3-Coated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Core-Shell Structured Cathode with Enhanced Cr Tolerance for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: However, the Cr-poisoning effect is a severe issue, causing electrochemical performance degradation.
Titulo: LaCrO3-Coated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Core-Shell Structured Cathode with Enhanced Cr Tolerance for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: For the development of a LSCF-based cathode with excellent Cr tolerance, a LaCrO3-coated LSCF core-shell structured (LCr@LSCF) cathode was prepared via the solution infiltration method.
Titulo: LaCrO3-Coated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Core-Shell Structured Cathode with Enhanced Cr Tolerance for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: After the cathode was coated with a LCr shell, the long-term stability and Cr tolerance were obviously improved, at the price of sacrificing some electrochemical performance.
Titulo: LaCrO3-Coated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Core-Shell Structured Cathode with Enhanced Cr Tolerance for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The development of a LCr@LSCF cathode with eye-catching Cr tolerance is of great significance to the commercialization of LSCF.
Titulo: LaCrO3-Coated La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Core-Shell Structured Cathode with Enhanced Cr Tolerance for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
